OL,3,CProtest planned over 'iconic' Lido
OL,4,Cafter owner negotiations break down
OL,6,FDeputy Warr claims a reserve bidder
OL,7,Fhas yet to have any conversations with
OL,8,Fstakeholders and users of the site
OL,9,Fduring a four-week "cooling off"
OL,10,Fperiod, which lasts until 31 October,
OL,11,Fleaving its future "at risk".
OL,13,FThe Lido is currently run by Jersey
OL,14,FProperty Holdings (JPH), the
OL,15,FGovernment's appointed landlord, which
OL,16,FDeputy Warr claims is not providing
OL,17,Fenough funding for the facility to
OL,18,Fremain open long-term.
